{"lemma":"ناضِرٍ","slug":"ناضِرٍ","root":"ن.ض.ر","root_slug":"ن-ض-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ض-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39999"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39999","headword_ar":"نَاضِرٌ","root":"nDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDiyrN","text_ar":"نَضِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDirN","text_ar":"نَضِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, L,) [being epithets from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDara","text_ar":"نَضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDura","text_ar":"نَضُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDira","text_ar":"نَضِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", respectively,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoDaru","text_ar":"اَنْضَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the K, but in the place of this we find in the corresponding passage in the L the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoDara","text_ar":"اَنْضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the addition “ is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDara","text_ar":"نَضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ” (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beautiful"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2809},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bright."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) So in the Kur, lxxv. 22,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wujuwhN yawomay^i*K naADirapN","text_ar":"وُجُوهٌ يَوْمَيِذٍ نَاضِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Faces on that"},{"kind":"text","text":"day shall be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful and bright:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shining by reason of enjoyment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a beautiful and pleasant and easy state of existence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.) [These epithets have also other, similar, significations, shown by explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDura","text_ar":"نَضُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its variations.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naADirN","text_ar":"نَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is coupled with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~N","text_ar":"غَضٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet applied to a boy, (A,) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDiyrN","text_ar":"نَضِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naADrapN","text_ar":"نَاضرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~apN","text_ar":"غَضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a girl, (A,) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDiyrapN","text_ar":"نَضِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and thus used are tropical. (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naADirN","text_ar":"نَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intense in greenness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru naADirN","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ نَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright, green"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,) like as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAqiEN","text_ar":"فَاقِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDu naASiEN","text_ar":"اَبْيَضُ نَاصِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and in like manner it is used as an intensive epithet applied to any colour: you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaru naADirN","text_ar":"اَحْمَرُ نَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright, red"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru naADirN","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ نَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright, yellow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) so says IAar: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASirN","text_ar":"نَاصِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to A'Obeyd, and Az adds,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glistening in its clearness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","L","K","Msb","TA","Bd","Jel","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}